  ● Regexp recompiled on every iteration
   ╭─[test.lis:6:32]
 5 │   for s in ["a", "b"] {
 6 │     let _ = regexp.MatchString("[0-9]+", s)
   ·                                ────┬───
   ·                                    ╰── compiled each time through the loop
 7 │   }
   ╰────
  help: Compile the pattern once outside the loop and reuse it: `regexp.MustCompile` for a known-valid pattern, or `regexp.Compile` to keep handling the error · code: [lint.regexp_in_loop]
